???: [――――]

Felt was keen to notice Yae's subtle reaction as she raised her eyebrows slightly.

The truth was, she was not sure. But in that helpless situation, she decided to cling to every last shred of hope, thinking that any further embarrassment would be insignificant.

One of them was the hope that the conversation between her and Yae might be overheard by something insignificant, which reminded her of the time when she had been made to face death, and the anticipation that came with it.

Yae: [Quiet.]

Yae opened one of her usually closed eyes and advanced toward the door of the room.

The overwhelming power of her words was enough to make Felt believe that if she made a careless move, a thread hanging around her neck would be pulled.

Because of that, the immobile Felt was left behind, and Yae reached out to open the door――but in that instant, a sharp sword tip pierced the door without a sound and mercilessly thrust toward Yae's throat.

Felt: [――Hk.]

Felt's breath caught in her throat as she saw Yae's white throat pierced by the sword ――but no. The tip of the sword stopped just before it sliced into her throat.

It was not her opponent who stopped. Yae managed to prevent the sword by entangling the tip with a thread.

It was a brush with death, but Yae was not out of danger yet. ――Another sword flashed, cutting through the door, creating a storm of slashing light.

Yae: [――――]

Faced with the oncoming storm of swords, Yae leaped backward and wielded her threads.

Despite one being a sword and the other a thread, the clash of the two weapons produced a satisfying sound like steel striking steel, filling the room with sparks of light that burned Felt's eyes.

Yae skillfully maneuvered her hands, releasing a volley of threads that filled the room, tearing apart the luxurious interior. However, her opponent also put on an impressive display of swordplay with both hands, cutting through the onslaught head-on, then forcefully sweeping aside the threads that were entangling their sword――,

???: [Gyaaaah!]

Yae: [――Guh.]

A front kick was delivered, landing squarely on Yae's slender waist. Yae twisted her body at the last moment and was thrown into a half-spin, landing on the floor with her feet against the wall and her hands pressed against her stomach.

Then, she stared directly at the intruder,

Yae: [What a ruthless guest you are, suddenly kicking a lady in the stom~ach!]

???: [――Is it necessary? You are a shinobi, so there can be no mercy.]

Yae: [Isn't that discrimination against Shinobi? That's not very gentlemanly behavior, now is it?]

???: [Unfortunately, I cannot recall a time when I was deserving of being called a gentleman. No matter the circumstances, I am nothing more than a swordsman, capable only of swinging a sword.]

That said, he flicked the threads from his swords and turned his calm blue eyes toward Yae. ――Hearing that self-assessment, Felt muttered, “Don't say dumb crap.“

To be sure, she did not know if he was a gentleman or not. However, simply calling one a swordsman was not enough. Felt knew that many would not accept such a description on its own.

Because the man who called himself a swordsman is the “Sword Demon” who once defeated the pinnacle of swordsmanship――,

???: [――Wilhelm Trias. Upon hearing that the kingdom was in dire straits, I came at once, despite my meager abilities.]

Upon hearing that introduction, Felt retreated to the corner of the room and sighed.

With unexpected reinforcements arriving, she was filled with extremely complicated emotions――,

Felt: […That Zodda-bug-niichan, you really don't hold back, do you? …What's with that guy from Emilia-neechan's place?]

With that, she muttered in equal parts amazement and admiration.
